name: Cameron Mulvey
position: Co-Founder, CEO @ Sute | Ex-JPM | Empowering Gen Z's Financial Future
about:
As the Co-Founder and CEO of Sute, I am passionate about empowering the next generation with financial literacy.

Everyone knows Gen Z loves learning from content creators, so we’re working with the best personal finance creators to host exclusive community-like Spaces, where our users subscribe for direct access to learn from their favorite finfluencers. In case you’re thinking it already, yes, this essentially makes us the OnlyFans of personal finance.

experience.title: Treasurer, Co-Founder
experience.description: The Watts 2 Boston Foundation is a non-profit organization that I have co-founded with my family. The aim is to provide monetary, educational, and occupational support and resources for young students living in Watts, California. Students in our program will receive funding for high school scholarships, making them more able to pursue a college degree. Then, they will work with our organization to find summer employment in Boston and will stay, likely with us, in the area for the summer.

experience.title: Intern
experience.description: This summer, I had the privilege of interning in three different departments for Cushman & Wakefield. I started in marketing, where most of my work centered around Adobe InDesign and Photoshop, creating materials and slides for brokerage pitches. Then, I moved to research, where I helped update the Microsoft Access database and created a "Research Spotlight," demonstrating the near negative correlation between rent increases and construction-adjusted tenant improvement concessions. Finally, I spent the end of my summer working on the Downtown Boston Brokerage team, where I compiled stacking charts and comparables for the downtown associates and directors.
